<section class="section">

<h2>
Research <span>Overview</span>
</h2>

<p>
Precision medicine microbiomics uses microbial community data to understand why individuals differ in disease risk, drug response, immune activity, metabolism, and clinical outcomes. Because the microbiome interacts with host biology, diet, environment, and therapeutics, it can provide an important layer of personalized health interpretation.
</p>

<p>
At PanorOmics, precision medicine is presented as a core microbiomics research area: a bridge between microbial ecology, host biology, pharmacology, immune response, biomarker discovery, patient stratification, and multi-omics precision health.
</p>

</section>

